node.text: Last night, we partnered with @MLB and @TeamGleason for an inclusive ceremonial first pitch in honor of Lou Gehrig Day. Watch as @stevegleasonofficial uses our Look to Speak technology to start last night's game. Try the app at the link in bio.

node.text:
“Pictures tell us about the world, so it’s important that they do that with a sense of accuracy and beauty that maps back to our real experiences.” — Florian Koenigsberger 

Florian leads our Image Equity Initiative, helping to make sure Pixel cameras capture everyone as they truly are. Learn more about our efforts to build a world where everyone belongs at the link in bio.

node.text: This #TeacherAppreciationWeek and every week we're thankful for all the educators helping future generations grow. You can thank an educator for their encouragement, inspiration and support by sending one of the ready-to-share thank you cards from today’s Instagram Story. Tap the link in bio to hear @CCSSO National Teacher Of The Year’s Kurt Russell share his story, the importance of the teaching community and ways we're showing.

node.text: "After it became clear that Live Transcribe helps me to communicate, it became clear that we could extend it to help others,” Googler Dimitri Kanevsky says about his work as a speech research scientist. Learn more about our efforts to build a world where everyone belongs at the link in bio.

node.text: From a glacier retreat at the summit of Mt. Kilimanjaro to coral bleaching in the Great Barrier Reef, today’s annual Earth Day #GoogleDoodle uses real time-lapse imagery from Google Earth and other sources to show the effect of climate change across our planet. Learn more at the link in bio. 🌎

node.text: Millions of people worldwide have speech and motor impairments that can make communicating difficult. Look to Speak was built to help people use their eyes to select pre-written phrases and have them spoken aloud on a mobile device. Learn more at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Illustrated Google Doodle for June 4, 2022 celebrating Pride month. On the left the frame is a brick building with a blue door, next to it is a circular insert image of a building with protesters. In the center of the frame is a headshot of Kiyoshi Kuromiya" an Asian man with dark hair, a goatee and a yellow collared shirt. To his right is a black corded phone next to a tree and the LGBTQ+ progress flag.

node.text: In celebration of Pride Month, today’s #GoogleDoodle honors the life of Kiyoshi Kuromiya — a civil rights activist who was influential in the movements for LGBTQ+ social justice, HIV/AIDS education and gay liberation.

node.text: Last night, we partnered with @MLB and @TeamGleason for an inclusive ceremonial first pitch in honor of Lou Gehrig Day. Watch as @stevegleasonofficial uses our Look to Speak technology to start last night's game. Try the app at the link in bio.

node.text: Nailed it 💅🏾 For National Nail Polish Day we’re featuring this #MySuperG, which showcases different shades from @peopleofcolorbeauty, a company that creates nail polish for people of color. Just a reminder to support small businesses that make life more vibrant.

node.text: Why build one pyramid when you can have 200? 🤯 Take a tour of Meroë in Sudan, home to an ancient burial ground that was once the heartland of the Kingdom of Kush. Explore more with us and @UNESCO at the link in @googleartsculture bio

node.accessibility_caption: An aerial view of the Google Bay View Campus, featuring several buildings surrounded by greenery and several roads. The two largest buildings feature sloping geometric roofs covered in solar panels.

node.text: Our new Bay View campus has opened — and it features a first-of-its-kind dragonscale solar roofing that’s equipped with 50,000 silver solar panels.  When combined with ​​nearby wind farms, these panels will allow Bay View to operate on carbon-free energy 90% of the time. The prismatic nature of the glass traps light that would normally escape from traditional flat solar panels — and has a unique sparkle, which helped it earn its name. Tap the link in our bio to learn more!  📸: @iwanbaan

node.accessibility_caption: An aerial view of the Google Bay View Campus, featuring several buildings surrounded by greenery and several roads. The two largest buildings feature sloping geometric roofs covered in solar panels.
An interior shot of a building at the Google Bay View Campus. Many colorful workspaces sit underneath a sloped, geometric, angled white ceiling.
A close-up of the unique solar panels of the "dragonscale" roof at the Google Bay View Campus. The reflective, shiny, diamond-shaped silver panels overlap in a way reminiscent of reptile scales.
Google logo artwork with Stacey Milbern on the left wearing pink glasses and pink colored blouse, next to a hibiscus flower, orange tree, and tiger.

node.text:
Today's #GoogleDoodle celebrates Asian Pacific Islander American Heritage Month by honoring Stacey Park Milbern on what would have been her 35th birthday. Stacey was a Korean-American, queer, disability justice activist, who also was a founding member of the disability justice movement. She dedicated her life to advocating for the LGBTQ+ and people of color within the disabled community. 

🎨: @art_twink

node.text:
“Pictures tell us about the world, so it’s important that they do that with a sense of accuracy and beauty that maps back to our real experiences.” — Florian Koenigsberger 

Florian leads our Image Equity Initiative, helping to make sure Pixel cameras capture everyone as they truly are. Learn more about our efforts to build a world where everyone belongs at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: A building at the Google Bay View campus, photographed across a small body of water at dusk. The roof is textured and geometric, featuring several sloped triangular peaks.

node.text: Take a look inside our new Bay View campus, which has officially opened to Googlers. It’s the first time we designed and developed one of our major campuses – and it takes sustainable building and workplace design to the next level with all-electric, net water positive buildings covered in "dragonscale" solar panels. Tap the link in our bio to learn more! 📸: @IwanBaan
